ITS HERE!!🥹🥰❤️😭🥳 I can’t wait for you all to read Jackie’s story!!😆👩🏾‍🎨❤️

It’s so surreal to finally hold my very first picture book!!! Shoutout forever to my incredible agent @wendilulugu, my amazing editor @msanniekelley, the fabulous art director @rachaelcole (who very kindly & lovingly held my hand through the entire process), and my phenomenal publicist @cynthia_elle for helping it get into the hands of readers!!

Books are a team sport, it seriously takes a village 🥵💪🏾 (& special shoutout to @stephaniehues for the purple scrunchie 😌💜)
Had a great signing at @bnphillypa (thank you so much to everyone who came!!🤗) followed by lunch with my favorite person 😌❤️!

Thank you so much @bankstreetlibrary for naming ✨Maybe An Artist✨ one of the Best Children’s Book of the Year and noting it for Outstanding Merit 🥹📚❤️!! I’m forever grateful for all the love my book has gotten, it truly means the world to me 💖!

Shoutout to my lil sis @lizatlarge (author AND illustrator) on her new books!! You worked really hard on these and it shows!!! ❤️🔥🥳🫶🏾 #lizatlarge #moretocome 

Link in bio for where to purchase!

✨JACKIE ORMES DRAWS THE FUTURE✨is ~officially~ out in the world!!🥳💐❤️

This book was such a labor of love and so much fun to make! I’m endlessly honored that I got the opportunity to share Jackie’s story and do it in such a bright and colorful way ❤️. Thank you again to Ormes & Jackson family and Nancy Goldstein for all your love and support with this project 💐.

(still mind blown that this is seriously my job 🥹☺️🥰🎨👩🏾‍🎨) #WomenInArt

The European Adventure has begun 😌

Ireland, you’ve been a dream!!🇮🇪❤️

Bella Venezia 🌹🎭😍

It’s so nice to be out in the world 😭!! This is the longest work break I’ve ~ever~ taken. 10 days in Europe initially felt impossible with my schedule but it turns out I can take a break and the world will keep spinning 🥲🙃 #whoknew 🤪
Last day in Florence 🌞🇮🇪❤️ We finished the night eating gelato at the Piazza de' Pitti and it was magical! 🍦😌✨

Grazie mille, Italia! ❤️🇮🇪

Tomorrow is our last day in Rome & the last day of our trip 🥲 (shoutout to my husband who’s the real MVP for planning and booking all of it 🥰). My feet will need a solid week to recover from all this walking but it was a 1000% worth it!!

MAYBE AN ARTIST is on my old high school’s summer reading list 🥹✨❤️!!

A decade ago I was 17 & going into my senior year absolutely terrified about the future and how uncertain everything felt (flipped through my old yearbook for the first time I’m forever and it was like going through a time machine 🤣). We’ve come a long way! 😭💕 (Thank you @emilycastor4 for showing me this!!🥰) #summerreading
See you Saturday @thebronxisreading !!🤓📚💕#bronxbookfest
Im doing a storytime & signing this Saturday at @bnphillypa 🥰👩🏾‍🎨📚 See you there!

MAGIC COMES TO BROOKLYN APRIL 2, 2024!!✨😭📚🌳🌆💖 (Pre-order links in my bio & stories!)

I’ve been working on this for the last few years and I’m so excited to finally show you all the cover for book #1 of my new middle grade @scholastic series, ✨SCHOOL FOR UNUSAL MAGIC✨!

I can’t wait for you all to meet these characters 😆❤️📚!! 

Shoutout to my incredible editor @jenne_with_an_e , the entire @scholastic team and as always the amazing @wendilulugu 🥰✨💕
I remember the Read Across America books from back when I was in school😭❤️!!! Such an honor for my book to be the August YA choice 🥹😆 thank you so much @neatoday! 📚💕
Galleys are here!! I can’t believe I’m finally holding this book 😆🌱💕🥹✨ SCHOOL FOR UNUSUAL MAGIC out April 2 (pre-order links in bio) ❤️

✨Maybe An Artist✨ has been out in the world for 1 whole year 🥳🥰😭😆🎊🎉!!!!

I will forever be so proud of this book!! I love being an author & I’m so grateful I get to tell stories for a living ❤️📚
👩🏾‍🎨 Author-Illustrator ✨
